  <static seed="1163" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/simplifyRationalExpressions90.pg">
    <statement><p>Simplify this expression.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{6t-30r}{t^{2}-25r^{2}}}=}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{6}{t+5r}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cross out common terms:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{6t-30r}{t^{2}-25r^{2}}} \amp = \frac{{6\mathopen{}\left(t-5r\right)}}{{\left(t-5r\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+5r\right)}} \\
                     \amp = {\frac{6}{t+5r}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
</solution>
